Use the standard library
This is how to largest_smallest_integers of lst:
  When lst's length is 0, then:
    The answer is [[], []]
  End when
  Remember that positives is []
  Remember that negatives is []
  Do this lst's length times:
    Remember that n is item 0 in lst
    When n is more than 0, then:
      Add positives to n
    End when
    When n is less than 0, then:
      Add negatives to n
    End when
    Remember that lst is item 1 in lst
  End do
  When positives's length is 0, then:
    Remember that biggest_negative is []
  But, if not:
    Remember that biggest_negative is min of positives
  End when
  When negatives's length is 0, then:
    Remember that smallest_positive is []
  But, if not:
    Remember that smallest_positive is max of negatives
  End when
  The answer is [biggest_negative, smallest_positive]
